radiates the light, must be moving. If it isn't,  

1499
02:27:12,720 --> 02:27:18,400
the emission of the light itself gives it a kick 
that moves it. Now, no matter what the quantum  

1500
02:27:18,399 --> 02:27:25,439
might have been, it loses energy in kicking the 
atom. That changes the situation instantly, and  

1501
02:27:25,439 --> 02:27:31,200
incidentally the 'color' of the light. Then, since 
all the radiating atoms won't be moving alike,  

1502
02:27:31,200 --> 02:27:38,559
etc., the mass of light can't be monochromatic. 
Therefore perfect interference is impossible.

1503
02:27:40,240 --> 02:27:44,880
"The way that relates to the problem in hand, 
is that we can't possibly destroy his energy.  

1504
02:27:45,680 --> 02:27:52,480
We can, as we do in the crumbler stunt, change it. 
He can't, I suspect, put too much power behind his  

1505
02:27:52,479 --> 02:27:58,319
crumbler, or he'd have crumbling going on 
at home. We get a slight heating from it,  

1506
02:27:58,319 --> 02:28:05,200
anyway. Into the bargain, his radio was after 
us, and his neutrons naturally carried energy.  

1507
02:28:06,160 --> 02:28:12,080
Now, no matter what we do, we've got that 
to handle. When we fight his crumbler,  

1508
02:28:12,080 --> 02:28:18,880
we actually add heat-energy to it, ourselves, and 
make the heating effect just twice as bad. If we  

1509
02:28:18,880 --> 02:28:24,960
try to heterodyne his radio—presto—it has twice 
the heat energy anyway, though we might reduce  

1510
02:28:24,960 --> 02:28:31,280
it to a frequency that penetrated the ship instead 
of all staying in it. But by the proposition, we  

1511
02:28:31,280 --> 02:28:37,920
have to use as much energy, and in fact, remember 
the 80% rule. We've got to take it and like it."

1512
02:28:39,359 --> 02:28:42,559
"But," objected McLaurin, "we don't like it."

1513
02:28:44,000 --> 02:28:49,120
"Then build ships as big as his, and he'll quit 
trying to roast you. Particularly if the inner  

1514
02:28:49,120 --> 02:28:55,120
walls are synthetic plastics. Did you know I 
used them in the 'S Doradus' and 'Cepheid'?"

1515
02:28:56,240 --> 02:28:57,679
"Yes. Were you thinking of that?"

1516
02:28:58,880 --> 02:29:04,720
"No—just luck—and the fact that they're light, 
strong as steel almost, and can be manufactured  

1517
02:29:04,720 --> 02:29:10,640
in forms much more quickly. Only the outer 
hull is tungsten-beryllium. The advantage in  

1518
