absorbed outside, and we'll radiate pretty fast,  

1519
02:29:17,120 --> 02:29:21,840
particularly as that tungsten-beryllium has a 
high radiation-factor in the long heat range."

1520
02:29:22,880 --> 02:29:23,680
"What does that mean?"

1521
02:29:24,960 --> 02:29:32,080
"Well, ordinary polished silver is a mighty poor 
radiator. Homely example: Try waiting for your  

1522
02:29:32,080 --> 02:29:37,760
coffee to cool if it's in a polished silver 
pot. Then try it in a tungsten-beryllium pot.  

1523
02:29:38,560 --> 02:29:44,960
No matter how you polish that tungsten-beryllium, 
the stuff WILL radiate heat. That's why an IP  

1524
